0032|#CODES LOAD <binary_file>  / BYTES=<N>
S   |            <           >          < >
0033|*loads <N> first characters of <binary_file> to the edit field
S   |       < >                     <           >
0034|*and lists them on consecutive lines below the current line.
0035|*Default value for <N> is BYTES=256.
S   |                   < >
0036|*The list of the characters has the following form:
0037|*CODES LOAD SORTCODE.BIN_
0038|*     0     0
0039|*     1     1
0040|*     2     2
0041|*     3     3
0042|*    ..    ..    .  .
0043|*    97    65    a  A
0044|*    98    66    b  B
0045|*    99    67    c  C
0046|*    ..    ..    .  .
0047|*where the second column gives the decimal code of the corresponding
0048|*character in the file. (For example, in SORTCODE.BIN, which is used
0049|*in alphabetic sorting, 97 is mapped to 65 (i.e. 'a' is like 'A').
0050|*Columns 3 and 4 are for explanations only.
