0131|- [HelpText]
0132|#COLX
0133|*COLX performs various modifications in the edit field.
0134|*COLX col1,col2 exchanges columns col1 and col2 for the
0135|*lines below the command (COLX) line.
0136|*Default is col1=0, col2=last column; i.e. the control
0137|*column and the last column are exchanged.
0139|*COLX Ri,Cj (where i and j are integers)
0140|*modifies the visible part of the edit field in such a way
0141|*that i lines and j columns are displayed. Typically
0142|*i<=23 and j<=80.
S   |  <         <
0144|*COLX Scol1,col2 copies characters in column col2 to
0145|*shadow characters of column col1.
0147|*COLX Li,col,j copies characters of line i to characters
0148|*in column col starting from line j.
0150|*Changing and hiding shadow effects (colors) in the edit field
0152|*COLX s<shadow_code>,<new_code>
S   |       <           > <        >
0153|*displays characters with <shadow_code> with another shadow code <new_code>.
S   |                          <           >                          <        >
0154|*The codes are given in decimal form, i.e. shadow `1' (red) is code 49
0155|*obtained by conversion 1(ascii:10)=49 .
0156|*For example, COLX s49,32 (red->blank) hides effects of shadows `1'.
S   |                               >
0158|*COLX s,<BIN_file>
S   |        <        >
0159|*converts all shadow codes according to a 256 byte binary file.
0160|*Default path for the file is <Survo>\U\SYS and extension is .BIN .
S   |                              <     >
0161|*Binary files are maintained by CODES SAVE and CODES LOAD commands.
0162|*For example, COLX s,SHADKILL hides all shadow effects, i.e. maps
0163|*all shadow codes to blank (32).
0164|*COLX s
0165|*restores original setting.
0167|- [New]
0168|*COLX w
0169|- [/New]
0170|*displays the current size of the main window in the form
0171|*COLX w 30 80 (window size)
0172|- shadow %: [LINK(q03_17.html)] [/LINK]
0173|*where 30 is # of lines and 80 is # of columns. (See also RESIZE?).
S   |                                                          %%%%%%
0175|*COLX W<integer>
S   |       <       >
0176|*gives the coefficient for waiting times in sucros. Default is COLX W10.
0177|*In tutorials (sucros) this coefficient can be changed temporarily by
0178|*'+' and '-' keys. '+' decreases and '-' increases its value.
0180|*COLX APU <word>=<value>
S   |          <    > <     >
0181|*sets a new line <word>=<value> in the SURVO.APU file. If the <word>
S   |                 <    > <     >                               <    >
0182|*line already exists, it's value is replaced by the new one.
0183|*COLX APUDEL <word>
S   |             <    >
0184|*deletes the <word>=<value> line from SURVO.APU.
S   |             <    > <     >
0185|*After COLX APU and COLX APUDEL the new contents of SURVO.APU is valid
0186|*when Survo is started again or a SETUP SURVO.APU command is given.
0187|- [New]
0188|*Alternatively, SYS is the same as COLX APU and SYSDEL is the same
0189|*as COLX APUDEL.
0190|- [/New]
